summary:
A corporate innovation professional who navigates the waters between different industries, seeking to use my varied experiences to bridge the gap between the entrepreneurial ecosystem and the corporate world. 
Over the past years, my work has included strategic business development, start-up mentorship, and corporate innovation. In particular, I have been designing, facilitating, and delivering innovation projects that instill intrapreneurial cultures in corporate settings. My entrepreneurial endeavors include co-founding "Chameleon Coworking" the first coworking space in New Cairo, and being the General Manager of "Unplugged", a renowned Egyptian web & mobile development house.

I backed up my experience with a Masters' degree in Innovation & Entrepreneurship from MIP Politecnico Di Milano (in Italy) and Solvay School of Management and Economics (in Belgium). 

I currently work with SODIC on their corporate innovation program to create an innovative and intrapreneurial culture in the organization.
